I think the video would overpower the audio if you connected them. For one, it has 68-ohm impedance, while audio has 150 ohms. And the video signal is mostly a full-modulation pulse wave at low frequency, very loud.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Tue Oct 01, 2013 11:32 am</p><hr />
